<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="230" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[343,473,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Tomocichla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,473,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Tomocichla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially considered part of the Regan’s 
<taxonomicName box="[982,1074,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Theraps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[982,1074,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Theraps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
section of 
<taxonomicName box="[1201,1335,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Cichlasoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1201,1335,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Cichlasoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,313,188,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Tomocichla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,313,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Tomocichla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in fast-flowing rivers and is one of the few genera of herichthyin cichlids found outside of northern Middle 
<collectingCountry box="[347,447,223,248]" name="United States of America" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">America</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Regan" box="[461,617,224,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" refString="Regan, C. T. (1908) A collection of freshwater fishes made by Mr. C. F. Underwood in Costa Rica. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 8, 2 (11), 455 - 464." type="journal article" year="1908">
Regan (
<number box="[550,608,224,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
initially proposed 
<taxonomicName box="[837,967,223,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Tomocichla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,967,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Tomocichla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the posterior placement of the pelvic fins. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bussing" box="[290,465,260,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" refString="Bussing, W. A. (1975) Taxonomy and biological aspects of the Central American cichlid fishes Cichlasoma sieboldii and C. tuba. Revista de Biologia Tropical, 23 (2), 189 - 211." type="journal article" year="1975">
Bussing (
<number box="[399,457,260,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
offers information on aspects of the taxonomy and biology of 
<taxonomicName box="[1210,1340,260,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Tomocichla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1340,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="230">Tomocichla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as comparisons with similar species and morphological variation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
